<br>
That being said, if we're dead set on upgrading ToK for us I think we should stick with the mana sieve idea.  I still think it's a better Shadow Knight ability, but I won't dwell on the idea too much. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->     I don't foresee Verant giving us a limited silence or an area stun, as they are either too difficult to program.  If it were actually changed to a useful form, this would be a valuable raid tool to augment an enchanter's ability.<br>
<br>
First, let's take a look at the stats of both our sieve and that of an Enchanter:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Mana Sieve</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Decrease Mana by 370 (L60)<br>
Mana Required: 150<br>
Casting Time: 3.0 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 8.0 seconds<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Decrease Mana by 100 (L60)<br>
Mana Required: 75<br>
Casting Time: 3.50 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 18.0 seconds<br>
Resistance Check: Magic<br>
<br>
Now to compare the rate of mana drain:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Mana Sieve</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mana drained per second: 27.925<br>
Mana drained per point of mana spent: 2.467<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mana drained per second: 4.211<br>
Mana drained per point of mana spent: 1.333<br>
<br>
This is of course assuming no resists on the Thunder of Karana (as Wulfhere pointed out, it actually resists about 54% of the time).  Factoring that in we get this summary:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana summary</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mana drained per second: 6.919% of Mana Sieve<br>
Mana drained per point of mana spent: 27.027% of mana Sieve<br>
<br>
I propose that Thunder of Karana be changed to this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana v3.0</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Decrease Mana by 150 (L60)<br>
Mana Required: 75<br>
Casting Time: 3.0 seconds<br>
Spell Recovery: 2.25 seconds<br>
Recast Delay: 8.0 seconds<br>
Resistance Check: None<br>
<br>
We would now be getting the following efficiencies:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana v3.0</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mana drained per second: 11.321<br>
Mana drained per point of mana spent: 2.000<br>
<br>
And the following summary:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Thunder of Karana v3.0 summary</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Mana drained per second: 40.541% of Mana Sieve<br>
Mana drained per point of mana spent: 81.081% of Mana Sieve<br>
<br>
We would need a bit over two people chain casting ToK to equal an enchanter's rate of mana drain, but oftentimes there simply isn't enough sieving to go around for a fast-paced raid.  This would alleviate a lot of stress from a single enchanter raid, and is still quite a fair bit more efficient than the current 7% we sieve compared to them.  However if there are enough enchanters, there will still be no need for us to cast Thunder of Karana as they are simply that much more efficient.<br>
<br>
Comments?<br>
